<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Prices must remain 'enticing' to attract cautious holidaymakers as more countries are added to the UK's coronavirus quarantine list, Jet2's owner said. </p>

<p>Dart Group said winter 2020-21 bookings have yet to match capacity cuts, although bookings for summer 2021 are 'encouraging'. </p>

<p>Suffering: Travel firms have been affected by the number of countries being placed on Britain's quarantine list</p>

<p>Travel firms have been affected by the number of countries being placed on Britain's quarantine list, with confirmation expected imminently that Portugal will be added again. </p>

<p>Wales and Scotland have imposed measures for arrivals from Greece. </p>

<p>Despite these 'setbacks', Dart has been satisfied with how well it is filling its places since resuming flights on July 15.</p>
